    "en": {
      "title": "24 company\u2019s interested in petroleum business in Sri Lanka: Minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Twenty-four company\u2019s from UAE, Saudi Arabia, USA, China, India, Russia, UK, Malaysia, Norway and Philippines have submitted proposals for the Expressions of Interest (EOI)s to engage in the petroleum business in Sri Lanka, Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera said.",
        "He said the committee appointed by the ministry will evaluate proposals, issue Request for proposal (RFP)s and finalize the process in 6 weeks.",
        "The Minister earlier said that they have called for Expressions of Interest for oil companies to import, distribute and sell petroleum products in Sri Lanka.(DSB)"
      ],
